===================================================
TEST RESULTS / ADJUSTMENTS
===================================================

It's hard to make more than 2 avocados worth without your bowls getting soggy. 
    So, if there's ever a need, you may have to switch bowls midway through. 

Common pitfalls: 
1) breading falls off 
    - avocado had too much egg wash on it
    - flour layer too thick 
    - forgot to freeze 
2) soggy fries. exterior soft, interior mushy 
    - overcrowding (steaming) 
    - temp too low (< 375F)
    - ate too soon (cheese didn't set 
3) burning 
    - rack too close to element
    - almond flour burns quickly, you should use mainly pork rinds / parm for outer layer (less almond flour in outer mix) 
4) blandness 
    - salt only in breading, not on fruit 
    - lack of acid (forgot the lime juice) 


